"Role-based access control should be at the heart of your governance, risk management, and compliance (GRC) strategy. Ivan Milenkovic of Atos Origin discusses the benefits, implementation risks of role-based access control and the organisational changes required in order to successfully implement it. He also gives advice on building the right business case and how to select correct methodology, frameworks, and solutions. This article provides guidelines based on extensive experience and focuses equally on processes and technology, since success is dependent on both. Today's mantra for information security is governance, risk management, and compliance (GRC). This ideal model, if implemented correctly, brings significant benefits to the security position of almost any organisation."
